In his candidate for presidency statement <tag name="PERSON" value="start"/>Kwa[niewski<tag name="PERSON" value="end"/>declared that he had graduated university studies. Actually he had never written his master thesis, nor passed the university final exams and therefore had no master degree. This came to light after the election.
In <tag name="DATE" value="start"/>December 2005<tag name="DATE" value="end"/> when his presidency was to end, he granted a clemency for a leftist politician <tag name="PERSON" value="start"/>Zbigniew Sobotka<tag name="PERSON" value="end"/>, who was sentenced for 3.5 years of prison for revealing a state secret (effectively, he warned gangsters about an operation against them). <tag name="PERSON" value="start"/>Kwa[niewski<tag name="PERSON" value="end"/>changed prison sentence to a probation.
